Privacy policy
Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 12/02/2025
1. Introduction
Oasis Land Development Limited, a registered company in the Cayman Islands (
Company #214607
), ("Oasis Land Development," "we," "us," "our") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting the personal information you provide to us when you visit and use our website,
https://www.oasis-land.com
(the "Website").
This Privacy Policy ("Policy") explains how we collect, use, protect, and share your personal information. By using the Website, you consent to the collection and use of your information as described in this Policy.
We reserve the right to update this Policy at any time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and we encourage you to review it periodically to stay informed.
2. Information We Collect
When you visit our Website, we may collect the following types of data:
a) User Information (Non-Personal Data)
IP address
Browser type and version
Device and operating system details
Website interaction data (e.g., pages visited, time spent on the site)
b) Personal Information (Voluntarily Provided Data)
Name
Contact information (email address, phone number)
Any details you provide when filling out forms, subscribing to our newsletter, or engaging in other activities on our Website
c) Additional Information
Preferences and interests based on your interaction with the Website
Communication preferences for marketing or promotional content
3. Purpose of Data Collection
We collect your data for the following purposes:
To understand your needs and improve our services
To personalise your experience on our Website
To send newsletters, promotional emails, and marketing communications that may be of interest to you
To detect and prevent fraudulent or illegal activities
To ensure compliance with legal and regulatory obligations
If you do not wish to receive marketing communications, you can opt out at any time by following the instructions in Section
8
below.
4. Data Retention Policy
We retain personal data
indefinitely unless you opt out
. If you wish to have your data deleted or removed from our system, you may request this by contacting us at
customercare@oasis-land.com
. Upon receiving an opt-out request, we will take appropriate steps to delete or anonymise your information.
5. Data Security Measures
We take data security seriously and have implemented industry-standard safeguards to protect your information from unauthorised access, data breaches, or misuse. These measures include:
Secure encryption technologies
Firewalls and access control mechanisms
Regular security updates and vulnerability assessments
While we strive to protect your data, no security system is completely impenetrable. Therefore, we cannot guarantee absolute security, and you acknowledge that you provide your information at your own risk.
6. Cookies & Tracking Technologies
Our Website
uses cookies and similar tracking technologies
to improve user experience, analyse website traffic, and tailor marketing efforts. These technologies help us understand user preferences, track website performance, and provide a personalised browsing experience.
You can manage your cookie preferences by adjusting your browser settings. However, disabling cookies may affect certain functionalities of the Website.
Third-Party Tracking:
We may use third-party analytics tools such as
Google Analytics and Meta Pixel (Facebook Pixel)
to collect and analyse usage data. These third parties may also use cookies to track user interactions.
For more information on managing cookies, visit your browser's help section.
7. Information Sharing & Disclosure
We
do not sell or rent
your personal information. However, we may share your data with:
Third-party service providers
who assist in Website operations, business activities, or service delivery. These providers are obligated to maintain confidentiality and use your information solely for the purposes they were engaged.
Legal and regulatory authorities
, if required to comply with applicable laws, enforce our terms, or protect our rights, safety, or the safety of others.
8. User Rights & Control Over Personal Data
You have the right to:
Access
your personal data
Restrict, update, correct, or delete
your data
Withdraw consent
to the use of your information for marketing purposes
How to Exercise Your Rights:
If filling out a form on our Website, look for an
opt-out checkbox
to withhold your information.
If you have already provided your data and wish to
modify or delete it
, please contact us via
email
at
customercare@oasis-land.com
.
To
unsubscribe
from marketing communications, follow the opt-out instructions included in our emails or contact us directly.
9. Children's Privacy
Our Website is
not intended for individuals under the age of 18
.
We do
not knowingly collect
personal information from minors.
If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected data from a minor, we will delete it immediately.
Parents or guardians who believe their child has provided personal information should contact us at
customercare@oasis-land.com
.
10. Disclaimer on Illustrations & Legal Advice
We strongly recommend that all prospective buyers seek independent legal counsel before proceeding with any land purchase.
Unless explicitly stated in an official government document, all images, red lines, pictures, and information on the Website are for illustration purposes only and should not be relied upon as exact representations of boundaries, measurements, or final property conditions.
11. Complaints & Regulatory Rights
If you have concerns about how we handle your personal data, you have the right to:
Contact us directly at
customercare@oasis-land.com
File a complaint with a relevant regulatory authority if you believe your data rights have been violated
We take privacy concerns seriously and will work to address any issues in a timely manner.
12. Contact Information
For any questions regarding this Privacy Policy or to exercise your rights, please contact us at:
